          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The isomeric ratios (IR) were measured in the isotones",
                " with N = 81 (135Xe,  137Ba, 139Ce, 141Nd, and 143Sm).",
                " Isomers with   J-PI  =  11/2-  were  excited  in  the",
                " reactions (n,g),  (g,n),  and b+ - decay of 139Pr and",
                " 141Pm. The    activation    methods   of   g-spectrum",
                " measurement was used. The marked difference of Ir was",
                " observed in  the  isotones  with the different atomic",
                " numbers Z but in the same reactions. The calculations",
                " of Ir   using   low-level   spectrum   and  radiation",
                " transitions on the base of the  quasiparticle  phonon",
                " model were  performed.  The satisfactory agreement of",
                " the measured and calculated Ir was obtained  for  all",
                " studied isotopes.  The  dependence  of  Ir  on  Z  is",
                " explained by the different  energy  of  reaction  and",
                " different probability   levels   population   of  the",
                " activation."
              ]
            }
          ],
